  "text": "Like most other cancers, GC has a multifactorial and multistep etiology that involves complex interplay among Helicobacter pylori (HP) infection, exogenous environmental and endogenous genetic factors [CITATION_1] . Persistent Helicobacter pylori infection, leading to chronic inflammation, plays a major role in gastric carcinogenesis and is preceded by a lengthy precancerous process, developing via multiple sequential steps [CITATION_2] .",
